Haldun Hadimioglu Papers

1989-2013 1 2 3 4 5 6
Biographical / Historical
Haldun Hadimioglu is currently an industry professor in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering at NYU Tandon. He began teaching in the Poly Computer Science department in 1985 and completed his Ph.D. in Computer Science at Poly in 1991.
Scope and Contents
Material covers records of Computer Science department meetings, faculty meetings, and specific committee meetings. Some meetings only have circulated agendas while others have related handouts and Haldun's handwritten notes.
Arrangement
Original order was maintained at the series and document level. Some folders are therefore chronologically non-consecutive.
Conditions Governing Access
Materials are open for research without restriction.
Conditions Governing Use
Permission to publish materials must be obtained from:
Poly Archives, Bern Dibner Library of Science and Technology 5 MetroTech Center Brooklyn, NY 11201 Phone: (646) 917-3943 E-mail: dibner.library@nyu.edu
Preferred Citation
Published citations should take the following form:
Identification of item, date; RG-043: Haldun Hadimioglu Papers; box number; folder/item number; Poly Archives & Special Collections at Bern Dibner Library of Science and Technology, New York University Libraries.
Immediate Source of Acquisition
Materials were received from Professor Haldun Hadimioglu on May 29, 2019.
